        Calculate the average temperature in the data represented by `parser`, but only for days at least as humid as `minHumidity`.
        Parameters:
        parser - the data to calculate the average temperature on.
        minHumidity - the minimum humidity to qualify a measurement for being in the average.
        Returns:
        the average temperature of the data `parser` represents. If no average possible, then return Double.NaN.

        Find the CSVRecord with the lowest value in the named `column` in the data.
